         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">17/4/82 ¶  ¶ From the N.Z. journal of science I learn, dear Mr Buchanan, ¶  that Epiblema grandiflorum has been found in the Northern Island of New Zealand; ¶  though this is very remarkable, yet the ...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">82.04.17a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To John Buchanan</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">A644, Mitchell Library, State Library of New South Wales, Sydney.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">17/4/82</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>From the N.Z. journal of science I learn, dear Mr Buchanan,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">John Buchanan (1819-1898).</p>
               </note> that <name key="Epiblema%20grandiflorum">Epiblema grandiflorum</name> has been found in the Northern Island of New Zealand;<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Buchanan (1882), p. 357.</p>
               </note> though this is very remarkable, yet the distribution of swamp-plants ranges in many cases so capriciously and widely, that in all probability your species is identical with ours.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Still I should like to compare a specimen from thence with some gathered by myself in West-Australia, if you will spare me one. If not already sent to Kew for identification I shall write a note on the subject for publication in New Zealand.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">No such publication has been found.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Epiblema%20grandiflorum">Epiblema grandiflorum</name>
            </p>
         </div>
